        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 4:53PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Buffalo, or 12 miles southeast of Point Pleasant,
moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Racine, New Haven, Middleport, Hartford City, Leon, Mount Alto,
Southside, and Letart.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
